Steps to Deploy React js application in ubuntu Instance using Nginx



1. sudo apt-get install nginx -y  


2. sudo apt-get install curl


3.curl -fsSL https://deb.nodesource.com/setup_14.x | sudo -E bash -


4.sudo apt-get install -y nodejs


5.cd /var/www/html/


6.sudo git clone (paste the url of frontend repo)


7.ls


8.sudo rm index.nginx-debian.html


9.cd frontend (enter into repo)


10.sudo npm install


11.sudo npm run build


12.sudo cp -r build /var/www/html (copy the build file to /var/www/html)


13.cd ../../


14.sudo mv build/* .


15.ls


16.There we can see files . so we can check with ip address only dont keep any port number end of the ip.


17.SG ports:     ssh:22 , React js :3000,  Http:80


18. Now we can see the frontend application Running successfully.
